      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, characterized by its individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS high-pressure variable valve timing. This chassis is paired with a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and the factory-spec M-variable limited-slip differential. Mechanical upkeep is current, including a proactive VANOS overhaul and a recent subframe reinforcement to ensure structural rigidity. The suspension remains tight, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration that provides exceptional turn-in and mid-corner stability. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains thermally efficient and delivers a visceral, linear power delivery all the way to its 8,000 RPM redline.",
